{#- ---------- macros ---------- -#}
{%- from 'macros.j2' import fill as _fill -%}
{%- macro fill(value, width='160px') -%}
  {{- _fill(value, width, 4) -}}
{%- endmacro -%}

{%- macro box(checked) -%}
  <span class="cb">{{ '&#9746;' if (checked is defined and checked) else '&#9744;' }}</span>
{%- endmacro -%}

{%- set L = lease | default({}) -%}
<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
<meta charset="utf-8">
<style>
  @page {
    size: Letter;
    margin: 42px 46px 72px 46px;
  }
  * { box-sizing: border-box; }
  body {
    font-family: Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif;
    font-size: 7.6pt;
    line-height: 1.28;
    color: #000;
  }

  /* ---- page 1 header ---- */
  .page1-header {
    display: flex;
    align-items: flex-start;
    gap: 0;
    margin-bottom: 3px;
  }
  .car-logo {
    flex: 0 0 72px;
    border: 1.5px solid #000;
    padding: 3px 4px;
    font-size: 6pt;
    font-weight: bold;
    letter-spacing: 0.8px;
    line-height: 1.5;
    text-align: center;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    margin-right: 8px;
  }
  .car-logo .reg { font-size: 5pt; vertical-align: super; }
  .page1-title {
    flex: 1;
    text-align: center;
  }
  .page1-title .main-title {
    font-size: 11pt;
    font-weight: bold;
    line-height: 1.25;
  }
  .party-lines {
    margin-top: 4px;
    font-size: 7.4pt;
  }
  .party-row {
    display: flex;
    align-items: baseline;
    gap: 4px;
    margin-bottom: 1px;
  }
  .party-label { white-space: nowrap; font-size: 7.4pt; }
  .party-line-field {
    flex: 1;
    border-bottom: 0.75px solid #000;
    min-height: 10px;
    font-style: italic;
    font-weight: bold;
    padding: 0 3px;
    font-size: 7.4pt;
  }

  /* ---- continuation page header ---- */
  .cont-header {
    display: flex;
    justify-content: space-between;
    font-size: 7.4pt;
    border-bottom: 0.75px solid #000;
    padding-bottom: 2px;
    margin-bottom: 4px;
  }
  .cont-header-left { display: flex; gap: 4px; align-items: baseline; }
  .cont-header-right { display: flex; gap: 4px; align-items: baseline; }
  .cont-label { font-weight: bold; }
  .cont-field {
    border-bottom: 0.75px solid #000;
    min-width: 180px;
    display: inline-block;
    font-style: italic;
    font-weight: bold;
    padding: 0 3px;
    font-size: 7.4pt;
  }
  .cont-date-field {
    border-bottom: 0.75px solid #000;
    min-width: 80px;
    display: inline-block;
    padding: 0 3px;
    font-size: 7.4pt;
  }

  /* ---- horizontal rule ---- */
  hr.rule { border: none; border-top: 1px solid #000; margin: 3px 0 4px 0; }

  /* ---- clauses ---- */
  .clause { margin: 0 0 4px 0; text-align: justify; }
  .clause-num { font-weight: bold; }
  .clause-title { font-weight: bold; text-transform: uppercase; }
  .sub { margin: 1px 0 1px 14px; text-align: justify; }
  .subsub { margin: 1px 0 1px 26px; text-align: justify; }
  .sublabel { font-weight: bold; }
  .bold { font-weight: bold; }
  .or-label { font-weight: bold; margin-left: 0; }

  /* ---- fill fields ---- */
  .field {
    text-decoration: underline;
    text-underline-offset: 3px;
    line-height: 1.1;
  }
  .field.filled { font-style: italic; font-weight: bold; }
  .cb { font-size: 8.5pt; vertical-align: -1px; padding-right: 1px; line-height: 1; }

  /* ---- tables ---- */
  table.grid { width: 100%; border-collapse: collapse; margin: 2px 0 4px 0; font-size: 7.4pt; }
  table.grid th, table.grid td { border: 0.75px solid #000; padding: 2px 3px; text-align: left; }
  table.grid th { font-weight: bold; text-align: center; }

  /* ---- footer area (rendered in HTML, not @page margin) ---- */
  .page-footer {
    margin-top: 8px;
    border-top: 0.75px solid #000;
    padding-top: 3px;
    font-size: 6.4pt;
  }
  .page-footer-inner {
    display: flex;
    justify-content: space-between;
    align-items: flex-start;
    gap: 8px;
  }
  .footer-copyright { flex: 0 0 200px; font-size: 6pt; line-height: 1.3; color: #000; }
  .footer-center { flex: 1; font-size: 7pt; text-align: center; }
  .footer-right { flex: 0 0 130px; text-align: right; font-size: 6.8pt; }
  .footer-initials { font-size: 7pt; margin-top: 1px; }
  .footer-reviewed { font-size: 6.8pt; margin-top: 4px; border-top: 0.5px solid #000; padding-top: 2px; }
  .eho-box {
    display: inline-block;
    border: 1px solid #000;
    padding: 2px 3px;
    font-size: 5pt;
    font-weight: bold;
    text-align: center;
    line-height: 1.3;
    vertical-align: middle;
  }
  .footer-form-id {
    font-size: 6.8pt;
    font-weight: bold;
    margin-top: 3px;
  }
  .footer-title-center {
    text-align: center;
    font-weight: bold;
    font-size: 7pt;
    margin-top: 2px;
  }

  /* ---- notice box ---- */
  .notice-box { border: 0.75px solid #000; padding: 4px 6px; margin: 4px 0; font-size: 7.4pt; }

  /* ---- signature block ---- */
  .sig-table { width: 100%; border-collapse: collapse; margin-top: 6px; font-size: 7.4pt; }
  .sig-table td { padding: 2px 4px; vertical-align: bottom; }
  .sig-underline { border-bottom: 0.75px solid #000; display: block; min-width: 100px; min-height: 14px; }
  .sig-label { font-size: 6.5pt; }

  .page-break { break-before: page; }
  .small { font-size: 6.5pt; }
</style>
</head>
<body>

{#- ============================ PAGE 1 ============================ -#}

{# ---- Page 1 Header ---- #}
<div class="page1-header">
  <div class="car-logo">
    CALIFORNIA<br>
    ASSOCIATION<br>
    OF REALTORS<span class="reg">®</span>
  </div>
  <div class="page1-title">
    <div class="main-title">RESIDENTIAL LEASE OR<br>MONTH-TO-MONTH RENTAL AGREEMENT</div>
  </div>
</div>

<div class="party-lines">
  <div class="party-row">
    <div class="party-line-field">{{ L.landlord_name | default('') }}</div>
    <div class="party-label">(&ldquo;Landlord&rdquo;) and</div>
  </div>
  <div class="party-row">
    <div class="party-line-field">{{ L.tenant_name | default('') }}</div>
    <div class="party-label">(&ldquo;Tenant&rdquo;) agree as follows:</div>
  </div>
</div>

<hr class="rule">

<div class="clause">
  <span class="clause-num">1.</span>&ensp;<span class="clause-title">Property:</span>
  <div class="sub">
    <span class="sublabel">A.</span> Landlord rents to Tenant and Tenant rents from Landlord, the real property and improvements described as:
    {{ fill(L.property_address, '320px') }}
    <br>{{ fill('', '420px') }} (&ldquo;Premises&rdquo;).
  </div>
  <div class="sub">
    <span class="sublabel">B.</span> The following personal property is included: {{ fill(L.included_property, '340px') }}.
  </div>
</div>

<div class="clause">
  <span class="clause-num">2.</span>&ensp;<span class="clause-title">Term:</span>
  The term begins on (date) {{ fill(L.start_date, '120px') }} (&ldquo;Commencement Date&rdquo;),
  <span class="sublabel">(Check A or B):</span>
  <div class="sub">
    {{ box(L.term_is_month_to_month) }} <span class="sublabel">A. Month-to-month:</span> and continues as a month-to-month tenancy. Either party may terminate the tenancy by giving written notice to the other at least 30 days prior to the intended termination date, subject to any applicable local laws. Such notice may be given on any date.
  </div>
  <div class="sub">
    {{ box(L.term_is_fixed) }} <span class="sublabel">B. Lease:</span> and shall terminate on (date) {{ fill(L.end_date, '120px') }} at {{ fill('', '50px') }} {{ box(L.end_time_am) }} AM &nbsp;{{ box(L.end_time_pm) }} PM.
    Any holding over after the term of this Agreement expires, with Landlord&rsquo;s consent, shall create a month-to-month tenancy which either party may terminate as specified in paragraph 2A. Rent shall be at a rate equal to the rent for the immediately preceding month, unless otherwise notified by Landlord, payable in advance. All other terms and conditions of this Agreement shall remain in full force and effect.
  </div>
</div>

<div class="clause">
  <span class="clause-num">3.</span>&ensp;<span class="clause-title">Rent:</span>
  <div class="sub">
    <span class="sublabel">A.</span> Tenant agrees to pay rent at the rate of $ {{ fill(L.rent_amount, '90px') }} per month for the term of the Agreement.
  </div>
  <div class="sub">
    <span class="sublabel">B.</span> Rent is payable in advance on the <span class="bold">1st</span>
    (or {{ fill(L.rent_due_day, '40px') }}) <span class="bold">day</span> of each calendar month, and is delinquent on the next day.
  </div>
  <div class="sub">
    <span class="sublabel">C.</span> If Commencement Date falls on any day other than the first day of the month, rent shall be prorated based on a 30-day period. If Tenant has paid one full month&rsquo;s rent in advance of Commencement Date, rent for the second calendar month shall be prorated based on a 30-day period.
  </div>
  <div class="sub">
    <span class="sublabel">D.</span> PAYMENT: The rent shall be paid by {{ box(L.pay_cash) }} cash, {{ box(L.pay_check) }} personal check, {{ box(L.pay_money_order) }} money order, {{ box(L.pay_cashier_check) }} cashier check, {{ box(L.pay_other) }} other {{ fill(L.pay_other_desc, '100px') }}, to
    (name) {{ fill(L.payee_name, '140px') }} (phone) {{ fill(L.payee_phone, '110px') }} at
    <br>(address) {{ fill(L.payee_address, '260px') }},
    <br>(or at any other location specified by Landlord in writing to Tenant) between the hours of {{ fill(L.payment_hours_start, '70px') }} and {{ fill(L.payment_hours_end, '70px') }}
    on the following days {{ fill(L.payment_days, '160px') }}.
  </div>
</div>

<div class="clause">
  <span class="clause-num">4.</span>&ensp;<span class="clause-title">Security Deposit:</span>
  <div class="sub">
    <span class="sublabel">A.</span> Tenant agrees to pay $ {{ fill(L.deposit_amount, '110px') }} as a security deposit. Security deposit will be {{ box(L.deposit_held_by_owner) }} transferred to and held by the Owner of the Premises; or {{ box(L.deposit_held_by_broker) }} held in Owner&rsquo;s Broker&rsquo;s trust account.
  </div>
  <div class="sub">
    <span class="sublabel">B.</span> All or any portion of the security deposit may be used, as reasonably necessary, to: (1) cure Tenant&rsquo;s default in payment of rent, Late Charges, non-sufficient funds (&ldquo;NSF&rdquo;) fees, or other sums due; (2) repair damage, excluding ordinary wear and tear, caused by Tenant or by a guest or licensee of Tenant; (3) clean Premises, if necessary, upon termination of tenancy; and (4) replace or return personal property or appurtenances. <span class="bold">SECURITY DEPOSIT SHALL NOT BE USED BY TENANT IN LIEU OF PAYMENT OF LAST MONTH&rsquo;S RENT.</span> If all or any portion of the security deposit is used during tenancy, Tenant agrees to reinstate the total security deposit within five days after written notice is delivered to Tenant. Within three weeks after Tenant vacates the Premises, Landlord shall: (1) furnish Tenant an itemized statement indicating the amount of any security deposit received and the basis for its disposition; and (2) return any remaining portion of security deposit to Tenant.
  </div>
  <div class="sub">
    <span class="sublabel">C.</span> No interest will be paid on security deposit unless required by local ordinance.
  </div>
  <div class="sub">
    <span class="sublabel">D.</span> If security deposit is held by Owner, Tenant agrees not to hold Broker responsible for its return. If security deposit is held in Owner&rsquo;s Broker&rsquo;s trust account, and Broker&rsquo;s authority is terminated before expiration of this Agreement, and security deposits are released to someone other than Tenant, then Broker shall notify Tenant, in writing, where and to whom security deposit has been released. Once Tenant has been provided such notice, Tenant agrees not to hold Broker responsible for security deposit.
  </div>
</div>

<div class="clause">
  <span class="clause-num">5.</span>&ensp;<span class="clause-title">Move-In Costs Received/Due:</span>
  <table class="grid">
    <thead>
      <tr>
        <th style="width:34%; text-align:left;">Category</th>
        <th style="width:16%;">Total Due</th>
        <th style="width:18%;">Payment Received</th>
        <th style="width:14%;">Balance Due</th>
        <th style="width:18%;">Date Due</th>
      </tr>
    </thead>
    <tbody>
      {% for row in L.move_in_rows | default([]) %}
      <tr>
        <td>{{ row.category }}</td>
        <td style="text-align:right;">{{ row.total_due }}</td>
        <td style="text-align:right;">{{ row.payment_received }}</td>
        <td style="text-align:right;">{{ row.balance_due }}</td>
        <td>{{ row.date_due }}</td>
      </tr>
      {% else %}
      <tr><td>Rent from &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; to &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; (date)</td><td>&nbsp;</td><td>&nbsp;</td><td>&nbsp;</td><td>&nbsp;</td></tr>
      <tr><td>*Security Deposit</td><td>&nbsp;</td><td>&nbsp;</td><td>&nbsp;</td><td>&nbsp;</td></tr>
      <tr><td>Other &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</td><td>&nbsp;</td><td>&nbsp;</td><td>&nbsp;</td><td>&nbsp;</td></tr>
      <tr><td><strong>Total</strong></td><td>&nbsp;</td><td>&nbsp;</td><td>&nbsp;</td><td>&nbsp;</td></tr>
      {% endfor %}
    </tbody>
  </table>
  <div class="small">*The maximum amount that Landlord may receive as security deposit, however designated, cannot exceed two month&rsquo;s rent for an unfurnished Premises, or three month&rsquo;s rent for a furnished premises.</div>
</div>

<div class="clause">
  <span class="clause-num">6.</span>&ensp;<span class="clause-title">Parking: (Check A or B)</span>
  <div class="sub">
    {{ box(L.parking_permitted) }} <span class="sublabel">A.</span> Parking is permitted as follows: {{ fill(L.parking_description, '260px') }}
    <br>The right to parking {{ box(L.parking_included_in_rent) }} is, {{ box(L.parking_not_included_in_rent) }} is not, included in the rent charged pursuant to paragraph 3. If not included in the rent, the parking rental fee shall be an additional $ {{ fill(L.parking_fee, '60px') }} per month. Parking space(s) are to be used for parking operable motor vehicles, except for trailers, boats, campers, buses or trucks (other than pick-up trucks). Tenant shall park in assigned space(s) only. Parking space(s) are to be kept clean. Vehicles leaking oil, gas or other motor vehicle fluids shall not be parked on the Premises. Mechanical work or storage of inoperable vehicles is not allowed in parking space(s) or elsewhere on the Premises.
  </div>
  <div class="sub">
    <span class="or-label">OR</span> {{ box(L.parking_not_permitted) }} <span class="sublabel">B.</span> Parking is not permitted on the Premises.
  </div>
</div>

{# ---- Page 1 Footer ---- #}
<div class="page-footer">
  <div class="page-footer-inner">
    <div class="footer-copyright">
      The copyright laws of the United States (Title 17 U.S. Code) forbid the
      unauthorized reproduction of this form, or any portion thereof, by photocopy
      machine or any other means, including facsimile or computerized formats.
      Copyright &copy; 1994&ndash;2001, CALIFORNIA ASSOCIATION OF REALTORS&reg;,
      INC. ALL RIGHTS RESERVED.
    </div>
    <div class="footer-center">
      Landlord and Tenant acknowledge receipt of copy of this page.
      <div class="footer-initials">
        Landlord&rsquo;s Initials (_______) (_______) &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
        Tenant&rsquo;s Initials (_______) (_______)
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="footer-right">
      <div>Reviewed by</div>
      <div>Broker or Designee {{ fill('', '60px') }} Date {{ fill('', '40px') }}</div>
      <div style="margin-top:3px;"><span class="eho-box">EQUAL<br>HOUSING<br>OPPORTUNITY</span></div>
    </div>
  </div>
  <div class="footer-form-id">LR-11 REVISED DATE 10/01 (PAGE 1 OF 4)</div>
  <div class="footer-title-center">RESIDENTIAL LEASE OR MONTH-TO-MONTH RENTAL AGREEMENT (LR-11 PAGE 1 OF 4)</div>
</div>

{#- ============================ PAGE 2 ============================ -#}
<div class="page-break"></div>

<div class="cont-header">
  <div class="cont-header-left">
    <span class="cont-label">Premises:</span>
    <span class="cont-field">{{ L.property_address | default('') }}</span>
  </div>
  <div class="cont-header-right">
    <span class="cont-label">Date:</span>
    <span class="cont-date-field">{{ L.agreement_date | default('') }}</span>
  </div>
</div>

<div class="clause">
  <span class="clause-num">7.</span>&ensp;<span class="clause-title">Storage: (Check A or B)</span>
  <div class="sub">
    {{ box(L.storage_permitted) }} <span class="sublabel">A.</span> Storage is permitted as follows: {{ fill(L.storage_description, '260px') }}
    <br>The right to storage space {{ box(L.storage_included_in_rent) }} is, {{ box(L.storage_not_included_in_rent) }} is not, included in the rent charged pursuant to paragraph 3. If not included in rent, storage space shall be an additional $ {{ fill(L.storage_fee, '60px') }} per month. Tenant shall store only personal property that Tenant owns, and shall not store property that is claimed by another or in which another has any right, title, or interest. Tenant shall not store any improperly packaged food or perishable goods, flammable materials, explosives, or other inherently dangerous material.
  </div>
  <div class="sub">
    <span class="or-label">OR</span> {{ box(L.storage_not_permitted) }} <span class="sublabel">B.</span> Storage is not permitted on the Premises.
  </div>
</div>

<div class="clause">
  <span class="clause-num">8.</span>&ensp;<span class="clause-title">Late Charge/NSF Checks:</span>
  Tenant acknowledges that either late payment of rent or issuance of a NSF check may cause Landlord to incur costs and expenses, the exact amount of which are extremely difficult and impractical to determine. These costs may include, but are not limited to, processing, enforcement and accounting expenses, and late charges imposed on Landlord. If any installment of rent due from Tenant is not received by Landlord within <span class="bold">5 (or {{ fill(L.late_grace_days, '30px') }}) calendar days</span> after date due, or if a check is returned NSF, Tenant shall pay to Landlord, respectively, an additional sum of $ {{ fill(L.late_charge_amount, '80px') }} as Late Charge and $25.00 as a NSF fee, either or both of which shall be deemed additional rent. Landlord and Tenant agree that these charges represent a fair and reasonable estimate of the costs Landlord may incur by reason of Tenant&rsquo;s late or NSF payment. Any Late Charge or NSF fee due shall be paid with the current installment of rent. Landlord&rsquo;s acceptance of any Late Charge or NSF fee shall not constitute a waiver as to any default of Tenant. Landlord&rsquo;s right to collect a Late Charge or NSF fee shall not be deemed an extension of the date rent is due under paragraph 3, or prevent Landlord from exercising any other rights and remedies under this Agreement, and as provided by law.
</div>

<div class="clause">
  <span class="clause-num">9.</span>&ensp;<span class="clause-title">Condition of Premises:</span>
  Tenant has examined Premises, all furniture, furnishings, appliances, landscaping, if any, and fixtures, including smoke detector(s).
  <div class="sub"><span class="sublabel">(Check one:)</span></div>
  <div class="sub">
    {{ box(L.condition_option_a) }} <span class="sublabel">A.</span> Tenant acknowledges that these items are clean and in operative condition, with the following exceptions {{ fill(L.condition_exceptions, '260px') }}
  </div>
  <div class="sub">
    <span class="or-label">OR</span> {{ box(L.condition_option_b) }} <span class="sublabel">B.</span> Tenant&rsquo;s acknowledgment of the condition of these items is contained in an attached statement of condition (such as C.A.R.&rsquo;s MIMO-11).
  </div>
  <div class="sub">
    <span class="or-label">OR</span> {{ box(L.condition_option_c) }} <span class="sublabel">C.</span> Tenant will provide Landlord a list of items that are damaged or not in operable condition within <span class="bold">3 (or {{ fill(L.condition_inspection_days, '25px') }}) days</span> after Commencement Date, not as a contingency of this Agreement but rather as an acknowledgment of the condition of the Premises.
  </div>
  <div class="sub">
    <span class="or-label">OR</span> {{ box(L.condition_option_d) }} <span class="sublabel">D.</span> Other: {{ fill(L.condition_other_desc, '260px') }}
  </div>
</div>

<div class="clause">
  <span class="clause-num">10.</span>&ensp;<span class="clause-title">Neighborhood Conditions:</span>
  Tenant is advised to satisfy him or herself as to neighborhood or area conditions, including schools, proximity and adequacy of law enforcement, crime statistics, registered felons or offenders, fire protection, other governmental services, proximity to commercial, industrial or agricultural activities, existing and proposed transportation, construction and development that may affect noise, view, or traffic, airport noise, noise or odor from any source, wild and domestic animals, other nuisances, hazards, or circumstances, facilities and condition of common areas, conditions and influences of significance to certain cultures and/or religions, and personal needs, requirements and preferences of Tenant.
</div>

<div class="clause">
  <span class="clause-num">11.</span>&ensp;<span class="clause-title">Utilities:</span>
  Tenant agrees to pay for all utilities and services, and the following charges: {{ fill(L.utilities_additional, '160px') }}
  except {{ fill(L.landlord_pays_utilities, '160px') }}, which shall be paid for by Landlord. If any utilities are not separately metered, Tenant shall pay Tenant&rsquo;s proportional share, as reasonably determined by Landlord.
</div>

<div class="clause">
  <span class="clause-num">12.</span>&ensp;<span class="clause-title">Occupants:</span>
  The Premises are for the sole use as a personal residence by the following named persons <span class="bold">only:</span> {{ fill(L.occupants_list, '300px') }}
</div>

<div class="clause">
  <span class="clause-num">13.</span>&ensp;<span class="clause-title">Pets:</span>
  No animal or pet shall be kept on or about the Premises without Landlord&rsquo;s prior written consent, except {{ fill(L.pets_exception, '240px') }}
</div>

<div class="clause">
  <span class="clause-num">14.</span>&ensp;<span class="clause-title">Rules/Regulations:</span>
  Tenant agrees to comply with all rules and regulations of Landlord, which are at any time posted on the Premises or delivered to Tenant. Tenant shall not, and shall ensure that guests and licensees of Tenant shall not, disturb, annoy, endanger, or interfere with other tenants of the building or neighbors, or use the Premises for any unlawful purposes, including, but not limited to, using, manufacturing, selling, storing, or transporting illicit drugs or other contraband, or violate any law or ordinance, or commit a waste or nuisance on or about the Premises.
</div>

<div class="clause">
  <span class="clause-num">15.</span>&ensp;<span class="clause-title">Condominium/Planned Unit Development:</span>
  {{ box(L.is_hoa) }} (If checked) The Premises is a unit in a condominium, planned unit, or other development governed by a homeowners&rsquo; association (&ldquo;HOA&rdquo;). The name of the HOA is {{ fill(L.hoa_name, '180px') }}.
  Tenant agrees to comply with all covenants, conditions and restrictions, bylaws, rules and regulations and decisions of HOA. Landlord shall provide Tenant copies of rules and regulations, if any. Tenant shall reimburse Landlord for any fines or charges imposed by HOA or other authorities, due to any violation by Tenant, or the guests or licensees of Tenant.
</div>

<div class="clause">
  <span class="clause-num">16.</span>&ensp;<span class="clause-title">Maintenance:</span>
  <div class="sub">
    <span class="sublabel">A.</span> Tenant shall properly use, operate and safeguard Premises, including if applicable, any landscaping, furniture, furnishings, and appliances, and all mechanical, electrical, gas and plumbing fixtures, and keep them clean and sanitary. Tenant shall immediately notify Landlord, in writing, of any problem, malfunction or damage. Tenant shall pay for all repairs or replacements caused by Tenant, or guests of Tenant, excluding ordinary wear and tear. Tenant shall pay for all damage to Premises as a result of failure to report a problem in a timely manner. Tenant shall pay for repair of drain blockages or stoppages, unless caused by defective plumbing parts or tree roots invading sewer lines.
  </div>
  <div class="sub">
